      "text": "## Your Replit Project: **Cognitive Taxonomy Protocol**\n\nThis is a **VS Code extension** that visually categorizes Python code into 5 color-coded architectural layers to accelerate code comprehension. It has two components:\n\n---\n\n### **1. VS Code Extension** (`cognitive-taxonomy-vscode-ext/`)\n\n**Core Concept:** Shifts code reading from slow \"System 2\" (linear scanning) to fast \"System 1\" (pattern recognition) using color-coded left borders on each line.\n\n**Five Categories:**\n\n| Color | Category | Purpose |\n|-------|----------|---------|\n| **Blue** | Blueprint | Data structures (classes, decorators, constants) |\n| **Green** | Plumbing | Infrastructure (imports, comments, setup) |\n| **Orange** | Transaction | Logic flow (functions, control flow, assignments) |\n| **Red** | Constraint | Hard limits (assert, raise, constants) |\n| **Purple** | Pedagogy | Documentation (docstrings, assessment markers) |\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Toggle:** `Ctrl+Shift+T` activates taxonomy view\n- **Hover Tooltips:** Explains what each line does architecturally\n- **Data Flow View:** `Ctrl+Shift+F` cycles through ASCII/Mini/Mermaid/SVG visualizations\n- **Sidebar Panel:** Shows cognitive load metrics (complexity score, balance score)\n- **AST Classifier:** Parses Python code and classifies each line by type\n\n**Architecture:**\n- `src/extension.ts` — Main entry point, manages decorations/commands\n- `src/astClassifier.ts` — Python parser + classifier (maps node types → categories)\n- `src/tooltipGenerator.ts` — Generates hover explanations\n- `src/sidebarProvider.ts` — WebView sidebar with metrics\n- `src/dataFlow.ts` — Data flow visualization\n\n---\n\n### **2. Website** (`cognitive-taxonomy-site/`)\n\nA marketing/documentation site with pages for Home, About, Install, Demo, and Wiki.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Demo File** (`demo_antigravity.py`)\n\nA sample **Derivatives Pricing Engine** (Black-Scholes model) demonstrating the taxonomy with color-coded sections for data structures, infrastructure, transaction logic, constraints, and documentation.\n\n---\n\n### **Academic Grounding**\n\nThe extension is based on:\n- **Kahneman (2011)** — System 1/System 2 dual-process theory\n- **Miller (1956)** — Working memory limit (7±2 chunks)\n- **Sarkar (2015)** — Syntax highlighting improves comprehension\n- **MITRE ATT&CK** — Taxonomy-based visual compression",
