      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Yes, based on everything we've discussed, **ProLector has the foundational architecture to work** — but there are specific gaps between what it currently does and what we conceptualized. Here's the honest assessment:\n\n## What ProLector Already Does Well ✅\n\n| Feature | Status | How It Works |\n|---------|--------|--------------|\n| **Teleprompter with WPM control** | ✅ Built | Adjustable 80-220 WPM, word-level scrubbing |\n| **AI Voice Read-Along** | ✅ Built | Kokoro-82M runs on CPU, sentence-by-sentence |\n| **Voice Cloning** | ✅ Built | SpeechT5 conditioning with F5-TTS models |\n| **Loop/Rehearse** | ✅ Built | Shift+click to set loop range |\n| **Multiple voice styles** | ✅ Built | 6+ voices including British options |\n| **Mirror mode** | ✅ Built | For confidence monitor glass |\n\n## What's Missing for the Full Vision 🚧\n\n| Feature | Status | What's Needed |\n|---------|--------|---------------|\n| **Visual prosody tooltips** | ❌ Not built | F0 pitch contour extraction, coarticulation bridges, vowel compression markers |\n| **Real-time keystroke triage** | ❌ Not built | Spacebar event logging mapped to AudioContext timeline |\n| **Synchronized recording** | ❌ Not built | MediaRecorder + AudioContext alignment |\n| **A/B contrast playback** | ❌ Not built | Side-by-side user audio vs. AI clone |\n| **Text-based punch-in editing** | ❌ Not built | Non-destructive cross-fade stitching |\n| **Regional dialect training** | ⚠️ Partial | Kokoro-82M has limited voice IDs; would need F5-TTS or XTTS v2 for Welsh/London/Notts |\n\n## The Core Question: Does the Science Support It?\n\n**Yes.** Everything we discussed — Dowrick's feedforward self-modeling, the own-voice benefit, multisensory integration, Hebbian myelination — is architecturally enabled by what ProLector already has. The voice clone + loop + WPM control trio is the minimum viable loop for procedural prosody training.\n\nThe missing pieces (visual tooltips, keystroke triage, A/B contrast) are **engineering extensions**, not architectural redesigns. The foundation is sound.\n\nWould you like me to start building the missing features?",
