      "text": "## Goal\n- Analyze, explain, and extend ProLector (a Replit-built teleprompter/voice training tool) while building a deep technical framework connecting LLM architecture, cognitive science, linguistics, and product design\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- User is an Italian speaker (likely from Nottinghamshire area) training English prosody\n- Prefers System 1 instinctive interactions over System 2 deliberative ones\n- Values first-principles reasoning and mathematical precision (\"esattezza\")\n- Skeptical of LLM confidence metrics; understands \"percentile confidence\" is simulated precision\n- Wants tools that work locally/offline where possible\n- Prefers \"mapped to daily context\" over rote memorization for learning\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- Located ProLector project at `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.gemini\\antigravity\\scratch\\prolector-yourvoice-perfected\\` (v2.0 main) and `Prolector-Google-AI-Studio-prototypee` (prototype)\n- Both repos backed up to GitHub: `andiekobbietks/prolector-yourvoice-perfected` and `andiekobbietks/Prolector-Google-AI-Studio-prototypee`\n- Full technical breakdown of ProLector's architecture (TanStack Start, Vite, Remotion, WebCodecs, Kokoro-82M, F5-TTS)\n- Identified and explained the Cognitive Taxonomy Protocol VS Code extension (separate project at `cognitive-taxonomy-vscode-ext/`)\n- Deep technical discussion covering: transformer attention mechanism, softmax, KV cache, autoregressive generation, forced alignment, cross-entropy loss, collocation probability\n- Identified four procedural language gaps in user's English: Romance syntactic flow, post-nominal modifiers, \"100 percentile\" usage, `sth` shorthand\n- Mapped Luca Lampariello's prosody-first methodology to ProLector features\n- Mapped Vinh Giang's 5 Vocal Foundations (Rate, Pitch, Volume, Melody, Pause) to tool features\n- Verified research backing for: Dowrick's Feedforward Self-Modeling, Lane's Self-Voice/ARROW, Hickok & Poeppel's Dual-Stream Model, 2026 AI Phonetic Self-Imitation studies\n- Explained why syllable-timed speech is cognitively exhausting for stress-timed listeners\n- Explained why LLMs almost always paraphrase (autoregressive branching drift, semantic vector blending, logit flatness)\n- Covered CEFR levels and C1/C2 reader capabilities for diagnosing AI-generated text\n- Covered Automation Bias (CRM/PF/PM in aviation as the structural solution)\n- Covered \"vibe citing\" and citation misattribution (42% rate in Google AI Overviews)\n- Covered faithfulness scores in RAG (still not 1.0 resolved; industry targets 0.85-0.90)\n- Covered SearXNG + LLM citation stack limitations\n- Covered NLI/SNLI model limitations with complex documents\n- Covered language attrition solutions (SRS solved math, LLMs solved immersion gap)\n\n### In Progress\n- Designing ProLector product features based on conversation insights\n\n### Blocked\n- Replit source zip not found on disk (may have been deleted or pushed directly to GitHub)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- ProLector should integrate Visual Prosody engine (coarticulation bridges, pitch peaks, vowel compression tooltips) driven by F5-TTS/ChatTTS internal alignment data\n- Hotkey triage must be single-key System 1 reflex (spacebar only) — no classification options\n- Voice cloning uses \"Auditory Feedforward Self-Modeling\" — not just utility but science-backed product positioning\n- Synchronized Dual-Track Timeline architecture: user audio + keystroke markers bound to `AudioContext.currentTime`\n- Non-destructive punch-in recording with cross-faded stitching (text-based patching, inverse of Descript workflow)\n- Regional dialect training possible via voice conditioning with local vocal archetypes (Welsh, London, Nottinghamshire)\n\n## Next Steps\n- Implement Visual Prosody tooltips in ProLector (intercept ChatTTS `[uv_break]` tokens, extract F0 pitch contours from F5-TTS, run forced alignment for coarticulation bridges)\n- Build hotkey triage system with `AudioContext.currentTime`-bound markers\n- Build \"Stumble Playlist\" auto-generation from flagged markers\n- Build A/B Contrast Playback (user recording vs. AI-cloned perfected version)\n- Build Non-Destructive Punch-In recording with cross-faded stitching\n- Reframe \"Clone My Voice\" feature as \"Auditory Feedforward Training\" with science-backed tooltips\n- Consider Accent Alignment feature using Speech-to-Speech voice conversion\n- Regional dialect voice conditioning (Welsh, London, Nottinghamshire archetypes)\n\n## Critical Context\n- User's location: Mansfield, Nottinghamshire, UK\n- ProLector tech stack: TanStack Start/Router, React 19, Tailwind CSS 4, Remotion, Vite 7, TypeScript, Kokoro-82M, F5-TTS, Chatterbox-Turbo, Fish Speech 1.5, ChatTTS, Pocket TTS, XTTS v2\n- User has Google Gemini access (scratch files were generated via Gemini/Antigravity)\n- The \"almost\" in \"LLMs almost always paraphrase\" is justified by: memorized sequences (temp=0), greedy decoding, named entities, code/syntactical constraints\n- Lexroom (Italian legal AI) raised $50M Series B — proved vertical AI works but requires cloud-tethered RAG, not purely local\n- Faithfulness in RAG is NOT solved — industry uses CI/CD grounding gates + live sampling + UX citation surfacing\n- Self-Attention Mechanism = 92% confidence as best replacement for \"the AI\" in precision prose; KV Cache = 85%; Context Window = 70%; Softmax = 60%\n- ProLector WPM benchmarks: TED 110-130, Tutorial 130-140, BBC News 150-160, US News 150-170, Audiobooks 150-160, Italian News 160-180+, Sports 250-400+\n\n## Relevant Files\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.gemini\\antigravity\\scratch\\prolector-yourvoice-perfected\\`: Main ProLector project (TanStack + Remotion)\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.gemini\\antigravity\\scratch\\prolector-yourvoice-perfected\\src\\routes\\index.tsx`: Landing page with TTS model comparison table and pricing tiers\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.gemini\\antigravity\\scratch\\prolector-yourvoice-perfected\\src\\routes\\teleprompter.tsx`: Core teleprompter with SyllabusMirror engine, word-level scrub, loop features\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.gemini\\antigravity\\scratch\\prolector-yourvoice-perfected\\src\\routes\\studio.tsx`: Video editing with WebCodecs demux, Remotion player, JSON EDL\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.gemini\\antigravity\\scratch\\Prolector-Google-AI-Studio-prototypee\\`: Earlier prototype (React + Gemini API + Express)\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.gemini\\antigravity\\scratch\\Prolector-Google-AI-Studio-prototypee\\metadata.json`: Gemini AI Studio metadata\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\cognitive-taxonomy-vscode-ext\\`: Separate VS Code extension project (not ProLector)\n- `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\demo_antigravity.py`: Sample file for Cognitive Taxonomy extension",
