      "text": "Now I have a good understanding of the ProLector teleprompter. It already has:\n- Token-based word tracking with timestamps\n- SyllabusMirror engine for TTS\n- Loop functionality (shift+click)\n- Voice selection\n- WPM control\n- Keyboard shortcuts\n\nNow I need to add:\n1. Visual Prosody tooltips - F0 pitch contours, coarticulation bridges, vowel compression markers\n2. Hotkey triage system (spacebar to mark stumbles)\n3. Stumble Playlist auto-generation\n4. A/B Contrast Playback\n5. Non-Destructive Punch-In recording\n\n\n6. I should start by examining the existing component structure to see how to integrate these features.",
