      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I have a complete picture of the codebase. Let me start implementing the features. I'll begin with:\n\n1. **Visual Prosody** - Add a prosody data layer to the Token type and render visual indicators\n2. **Hotkey Triage** - Spacebar to flag stumbles, storing markers at AudioContext.currentTime\n3. **Stumble Playlist** - Auto-generate loop ranges from flagged markers\n4. **A/B Contrast Playback** - Side-by-side user audio vs AI clone\n5. **Non-Destructive Punch-In** - Cross-fade stitching\n\n\n6. **Prosody Overlay** - I'm extending the Token type with prosody data like pitch peaks, stress, and coarticulation bridges, then building a new component to render this as a subtle visual layer beneath each word. I'll also add a hook to manage prosody state and integrate it into the main transcript stage.\n\nNow I'm moving on to the triage and playlist features, starting with a hook to track stumble markers with timestamps, then building an auto-generation system that converts those markers into loop ranges. I'll add a UI panel to display the playlist and implement the A/B contrast and punch-in recording capabilities with cross-fade support.",
