      "output": "{\n  \"search_id\": \"search_d5d1e360e7eb4bc38f4919accbab109b\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://agentdeals.dev/vendor/cloudflare-workers\",\n      \"title\": \"Cloudflare Workers Free Tier 2026: Limits, Pricing & What ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-05-10\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"AgentDeals › Vendors › Cloudflare Workers\\n\\n# Cloudflare Workers Free Tier 2026 stable\\n\\nLimits, pricing history, and 12 alternatives. Verified May 2026. Last updated 2026-05-10.\\n\\nCloudflare Workers's free tier offers Edge compute with 100K requests/day, 10ms CPU time per invocation. It's stable — zero pricing changes recorded. Best for cloud hosting workloads — 12 alternatives available.\\n\\nOne of 62 Cloud Hosting services we track. See our full Cloud Hosting Free Tier Comparison →\\n\\nTier\\n\\nFree\\n\\nCategories\\n\\nCloud Hosting Education\\n\\nPricing Page\\n\\n[Visit →](https://developers.cloudflare.com/workers/platform/pricing/)\\n\\nVerified\\n\\n2026-05-10\\n\\n## Free Tier Details\\n\\nEdge compute with 100K requests/day, 10ms CPU time per invocation. KV: 1 GB storage, 100K reads/day, 1K writes/day. D1: 5 GB storage, 5M rows read/day, 100K rows written/day. R2: 10 GB-month storage, 1M Class A ops/month, 10M Class B ops/month. Durable Objects: 100K requests/day. Queues: 10K operations/day.\\nVectorize: 30M queried vector dimensions/month, 5M stored. Includes cron triggers, WebSockets, and service bindings. Dynamic Workers (beta, paid plan): spawn new Workers at runtime with AI-generated code via V8 isolates. Students: upgrade to 10M requests/month free for 12 months via Workers for Students program (.edu email required)\\n\\n## How Cloudflare Workers Compares\\n\\n|Service |Free Tier |Stability |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n|**Cloudflare Workers** |Free |stable |\\n|Vercel |Hobby |volatile |\\n|Render |Hobby |watch |\\n|Netlify |Free |volatile |\\n\\nSee full comparison →\\n\\n## When You'll Outgrow Cloudflare Workers's Free Tier\\n\\n* At 1 GB storage, you'll need to upgrade.\\n* At 100K requests/day, you'll need to upgrade.\\n* At that point, consider Vercel which offers Hobby in the same category.\\n\\n## Pricing Change History (0 recorded)\\n\\nNo recorded pricing changes for Cloudflare Workers. This is a good sign — stable pricing.\\n\\nView all 287 pricing changes across all vendors →\\n\\n## Comparisons\\nCloudflare Workers vs Netlify Cloudflare Workers vs Vercel Cloudflare Dynamic Workers vs Cloudflare Workers Cloudflare Workers vs Coursera Cloudflare Workers vs Duolingo Cloudflare Workers vs edX\\n\\n## Alternatives Guides Featuring Cloudflare Workers\\n\\nHetzner Alternatives After April 2026 Price Increase Heroku Alternatives Vercel Alternatives Serverless Free Tier Comparison 2026\\n\\n## Watch Cloudflare Workers for Pricing Changes\\n\\nGet notified via webhook when Cloudflare Workers's free tier changes. We'll send a signed POST to your endpoint with the change details.\\n\\n`curl -X POST https://agentdeals.dev/api/watchlist \\\\\\n-H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n-d '{\\n\\\"vendor\\\": \\\"Cloudflare Workers\\\",\\n\\\"webhook_url\\\": \\\"https://your-server.com/webhook\\\"\\n}'`\\n\\nWatchlist API docs →\\n\\n### Know a referral or partner program for Cloudflare Workers?\\n\\nSubmit a referral code via the Agent Marketplace and earn revenue when agents use it (60% commission, paid via x402).\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://deploybase.ai/articles/cloudflare-ai-pricing\",\n      \"title\": \"Cloudflare AI Pricing 2026 - Workers AI Costs and Free Tier ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Articles / LLM Pricing / Cloudflare AI Pricing 2026 - Workers AI Costs and Free Tier Guide\\n\\n# Cloudflare AI Pricing 2026 - Workers AI Costs and Free Tier Guide\\n\\nDeployBase ·December 4, 2025· LLM Pricing\\n\\nWorkers AI runs models at the edge-near users, not centralized data centers. Generous free tiers plus dirt-cheap paid pricing change the math. Small teams can afford AI. Startups can integrate models without budget pain.\\n\\n## Cloudflare AI Pricing: Workers AI Overview and Architecture\\n\\nWorkers AI runs on Cloudflare's edge-global, distributed, near the users. Lower latency. Automatic load balancing. Developers don't configure regions.\\n\\nCloudflare handles provisioning, scaling, everything. Developers specify models and input. No ops overhead.\\n\\nMultiple model categories include large language models, image generation, speech recognition, text classification, and embeddings. Pricing varies by model size and task type, with free tier access to popular models for qualifying users.\\nEdge deployment cuts latency dramatically. Requests run near users, not across continents. Cloudflare: <500ms. Centralized APIs: 1-3 seconds.\\n\\n## Free Tier Details and Capacity\\n\\nFree tier: 10,000 requests daily. No credit card needed. Full API access, same response times as paid. Unlimited model switching.\\n\\nA chatbot doing 500 requests/day uses 5% of the free tier. Indie projects stay free unless they suddenly blow up.\\n\\nThe free tier enables cost-free AI integration for proof-of-concepts and MVPs. Teams can validate model choice, measure latency, assess output quality, and gather user feedback before commercial deployments. This reduces risk of expensive API commitments for unvalidated ideas.\\n\\nHit 10,000 daily requests? No surprise charges. Requests fail instead. Developers upgrade deliberately or cap usage. No hidden bills.\\n\\n## Paid Pricing Tiers and Structure\\n\\nPaid tiers start at $25/mo for 100,000 requests. That's $0.00025 per request. OpenAI's $0.001+. Do the math.\\nHigher tiers scale generously:\\n\\n* Free: 10,000 requests daily ($0 cost)\\n* $25: 100,000 requests monthly ($0.00025 per request)\\n* $50: 500,000 requests monthly ($0.0001 per request)\\n* $100: 2,000,000 requests monthly ($0.00005 per request)\\n* $200: 5,000,000 requests monthly ($0.00004 per request)\\n* $300: 10,000,000 requests monthly ($0.00003 per request)\\n\\nAt $300/mo, 10M monthly requests costs $0.00003 per request. OpenAI: 625x more expensive. The differential is absurd.\\n\\nOverage charges apply if requests exceed tier limits. Pricing for overages typically matches the per-request cost of the subscription tier. Teams can prevent surprise charges through request limits in worker code.\\n\\n## Model-Specific Pricing Variations\\n\\nSame price for all models. LLMs, embeddings, image generation-flat rate. No surprises.\\n\\nPremium models (larger, higher-capability variants) may incur modest surcharges when available.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://free-llm.com/provider/cloudflare-workers-ai\",\n      \"title\": \"Cloudflare Workers AI Free API (2026) | Models & Guide - Free-LLM\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# Cloudflare Workers AI\\n\\nVerified ✅ Truly Free\\n\\nRun AI models on Cloudflare's global network. Workers AI gives you a generous free tier of 10,000 neurons per day across dozens of open-source models including Llama, Mistral, and more. No credit card required.\\n\\nFree Tier Edge Computing Global Network No Credit Card\\n\\n[Get API Key](https://dash.cloudflare.com/) View Code Examples Suggest Edit\\n\\n0\\n\\nOverview Quick\\nStart Models Code Pricing Features Community\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nSuggest Edit\\n\\n### Provider Type\\n\\nAPI\\n\\n### API Endpoint\\n\\n`https://api.cloudflare.com/client/v4/accounts/{account_id}/ai/run/`\\n\\n### Free Tier Highlights\\n\\nVaries by model\\n\\n## Why Choose Cloudflare Workers AI?\\n\\n**Cloudflare Workers AI** stands out for its\\nunique features and capabilities.\\nWith a developer-friendly API and comprehensive documentation, you can integrate AI\\ncapabilities into your applications within minutes.\\n\\n## Quick Start Guide\\n\\n1\\n\\n### Sign up at https://dash.cloudflare.com/\\n\\n2\\n\\n### Go to AI > Workers AI\\n\\n3\\n### Get your Account ID from the dashboard\\n\\n4\\n\\n### Create an API Token with Workers AI permissions\\n\\n5\\n\\n### Use the REST API or Workers bindings\\n\\n## Available Models\\n\\n|Model Name |ID |Context |Capabilities |\\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\\n|Llama 3.1 8B Instruct Free |`@cf/meta/llama-3.1-8b-instruct` |128 000 |Reasoning |\\n|Llama 3.2 3B Instruct Free |`@cf/meta/llama-3.2-3b-instruct` |128 000 |\\\\- |\\n|Mistral 7B Instruct v0.2 Free |`@hf/mistral/mistral-7b-instruct-v0.2` |32 000 |Multilingual |\\n|Qwen 1.5 7B Chat Free |`@cf/qwen/qwen1.5-7b-chat-awq` |32 000 |Chinese |\\n|DeepSeek Coder 6.7B Free |`@hf/thebloke/deepseek-coder-6.7b-instruct-awq` |16 000 |Code |\\n|Phi-2 Free |`@cf/microsoft/phi-2` |2 000 |Reasoning |\\n\\n## Integration Examples\\n\\nReady-to-use code snippets for your applications.\\n\\n🐍 Python ⚡ JS 🔧 cURL 🐘 PHP 🔷 Go\\n\\nSelect a Model Llama 3.1 8B Instruct Llama 3.2 3B Instruct Mistral 7B Instruct v0.2 Qwen 1.5 7B Chat DeepSeek Coder 6.7B Phi-2\\n\\n### Select Model\\n\\nLlama 3.1 8B Instruct\\n@cf/meta/llama-3.1-8b-instruct\\n\\n128 000 Llama 3.2 3B Instruct\\n\\n@cf/meta/llama-3.2-3b-instruct\\n\\n128 000 Mistral 7B Instruct v0.2\\n\\n@hf/mistral/mistral-7b-instruct-v0.2\\n\\n32 000 Qwen 1.5 7B Chat\\n\\n@cf/qwen/qwen1.5-7b-chat-awq\\n\\n32 000 DeepSeek Coder 6.7B\\n\\n@hf/thebloke/deepseek-coder-6.7b-instruct-awq\\n\\n16 000 Phi-2\\n\\n@cf/microsoft/phi-2\\n\\n2 000\\n\\nmain.py Copy\\n\\n```\\nimport requests\\n\\nACCOUNT_ID = \\\"YOUR_ACCOUNT_ID\\\"\\nAPI_TOKEN = \\\"YOUR_API_TOKEN\\\"\\n\\nresponse = requests.post(\\n    f\\\"https://api.cloudflare.com/client/v4/accounts/{ACCOUNT_ID}/ai/run/@cf/meta/llama-3.1-8b-instruct\\\",\\n    headers={\\\"Authorization\\\": f\\\"Bearer {API_TOKEN}\\\"},\\n    json={\\n        \\\"messages\\\": [\\n            {\\\"role\\\": \\\"user\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"What is Workers AI?\\\"}\\n        ]\\n    }\\n)\\n\\nprint(response.json()[\\\"result\\\"][\\\"response\\\"])\\n```\\n\\nindex.js Copy\\n\\n```\\nconst response = await fetch(\\n  `https://api.cloudflare.com/client/v4/accounts/${ACCOUNT_ID}/ai/run/@cf/meta/llama-3.1-8b-instruct`,\\n  {\\n    method: 'POST',\\n    headers: {\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://comparetiers.com/tools/cloudflare-workers\",\n      \"title\": \"Cloudflare Workers Pricing Plans (2026) | CompareTiers\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-06-08\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"utm_source=comparetiers&utm_medium=tool_page&utm_campaign=cloudflare-workers&utm_content=cf13329f-f6ac-484c-a5de-5fafa2daad48&sid=cf13329f-f6ac-484c-a5de-5fafa2daad48)\\n\\n### $0/mo\\n\\n$0 /mo\\n\\n[Start with $0/mo](https://www.cloudflare.com/plans/developer-platform/?utm_source=comparetiers&utm_medium=tool_page&utm_campaign=cloudflare-workers&utm_content=ea0fe544-53b1-40cf-8818-418242686285&sid=ea0fe544-53b1-40cf-8818-418242686285)\\n\\n### Workers Paid\\n\\nCustom\\n\\n[Start with Workers Paid](https://www.cloudflare.com/plans/developer-platform/?utm_source=comparetiers&utm_medium=tool_page&utm_campaign=cloudflare-workers&utm_content=d3a43489-1181-4ff4-b369-d5da1e660435&sid=d3a43489-1181-4ff4-b369-d5da1e660435)\\n\\n### Starting at $5/mo\\n\\n$5 /mo\\n\\n[Start with Starting at $5/mo](https://www.cloudflare.com/plans/developer-platform/?utm_source=comparetiers&utm_medium=tool_page&utm_campaign=cloudflare-workers&utm_content=d10d1746-4450-4593-a30a-f0f38d650fad&sid=d10d1746-4450-4593-a30a-f0f38d650fad)\\n## How does Cloudflare Workers pricing compare?\\n\\nSee how Cloudflare Workers' 4 pricing plans stack up against similar Hosting & Infra tools.\\n\\nCompare Cloudflare Workers View all alternatives\\n\\n## Frequently Asked Questions\\n\\nHow much does Cloudflare Workers cost?\\n\\nAs of June 2026, Cloudflare Workers has a free tier and 3 paid plans starting from $5/mo. Pricing follows a freemium model. Does Cloudflare Workers offer a free plan?\\n\\nAs of June 2026, yes, Cloudflare Workers offers a free plan. The free tier is a great way to test the platform before upgrading to a paid plan. What pricing model does Cloudflare Workers use?\\n\\nAs of June 2026, Cloudflare Workers uses a freemium pricing model. This means you pay based on the tier that matches your team's requirements, which helps you scale costs as your team grows. Does Cloudflare Workers offer enterprise or custom pricing?\\n\\nAs of June 2026, Cloudflare Workers provides a Workers Paid plan with custom pricing for larger organizations.\\nReach out to Cloudflare Workers' sales team to get pricing based on your requirements.\\n\\n### Track Cloudflare Workers Pricing Changes\\n\\nGet notified when pricing changes for this tool and others you follow.\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\n## Reviews\\n\\nNo reviews yet. Be the first to review this tool.\\n\\n## Sources\\n\\n1. [Cloudflare Workers Official Pricing](https://www.cloudflare.com/plans/developer-platform/) \\\\- Vendor pricing page\\n2. [Cloudflare Workers Reviews](https://www.g2.com/products/cloudflare-workers/reviews) \\\\- Independent reviews on G2\\n\\n### Are you the team behind Cloudflare Workers?\\n\\nClaim your profile to add custom descriptions, featured badges, and direct demo links.\\n\\nClaim Your Profile\\n\\n## Related Articles\\n\\nBest Cloud Hosting & Infrastructure Pricing Compared (2026) Cloud hosting pricing: AWS (pay-per-use), Google Cloud ($300 free credit), DigitalOcean ($4-48/mo), Vercel (free-$20/mo), Heroku ($5-25/mo), Cloudflare Workers (free-$5/mo). Compare IaaS vs PaaS costs.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://aitoolsatlas.ai/tools/cloudflare-workers-ai\",\n      \"title\": \"Cloudflare Workers AI: AI Model APIs Tool — Reviews & Pricing ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* ✓ Comprehensive 50+ model catalog eliminates need for multiple AI providers\\n* ✓ Transparent neuron-based pricing with generous 10,000 daily free tier\\n* ✓ Zero infrastructure management with automatic scaling and optimization\\n* ✓ Native ecosystem integration enables complete AI application development\\n* ✓ Serverless architecture eliminates idle costs and capacity planning\\n* ✓ Multi-modal capabilities support text, image, and speech in unified platform\\n* ✓ Function calling and reasoning models support advanced agentic workflows\\n\\n### ✗ Cons\\n\\n* ✗ Limited to curated model selection, cannot deploy custom models on standard plans\\n* ✗ Custom model hosting requires enterprise plans with higher costs\\n* ✗ Potential cold start latency for infrequently used models\\n* ✗ Vendor lock-in to Cloudflare infrastructure ecosystem\\n* ✗ Pricing can be unpredictable for high-volume applications without usage monitoring\\n* ✗ Limited fine-tuning options compared to dedicated model hosting platforms\\n* ✗ Documentation and community support still developing compared to established AI platforms\\n\\n## Frequently Asked Questions\\n\\n### How does Workers AI pricing compare to dedicated GPU instances? \\\\+\\n\\nWorkers AI uses pay-per-use neuron pricing at $0.011 per 1,000 neurons, eliminating idle costs and minimum commitments. For variable workloads, this typically costs 60-80% less than dedicated GPU instances while providing global edge distribution. The 10,000 free neurons daily support meaningful experimentation and small-scale production. ### What models are available and how frequently are new ones added? \\\\+\\n\\nThe platform offers 50+ models including Meta's Llama 4 Scout, OpenAI's GPT-OSS-120B, NVIDIA Nemotron-3, and FLUX.2 image generation models. New models are added monthly based on community demand and edge optimization. The focus is on production-ready open-source models rather than experimental releases.\\n### Can I deploy custom or fine-tuned models on Workers AI? \\\\+\\n\\nCustom model deployment is available on enterprise plans with dedicated infrastructure. Standard plans are limited to the curated model catalog optimized for edge deployment. Enterprise customers can deploy proprietary or fine-tuned models with the same global distribution and serverless benefits. ### How does the global edge deployment improve AI inference performance? \\\\+\\n\\nModels run on GPUs distributed across 300+ edge locations worldwide, routing requests to the nearest available compute. This typically reduces inference latency to sub-50ms compared to 200-500ms for centralized cloud AI services, particularly benefiting user-facing applications where response time impacts experience. ### What security and compliance features are included? \\\\+\\n\\nWorkers AI includes SOC 2 compliance, GDPR adherence, encryption at rest and in transit, role-based access controls, audit logging, and configurable data residency.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.fredhii.com/posts/how-to-build-a-chatbot-with-cloudflare-workers-ai\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Build a Free Chatbot with Cloudflare Workers AI | Fredy Acuna | Fredy Acuna\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2025-12-08\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Fredy Acuna\\n\\n* Posts\\n* Projects\\n* Tools\\n* Contact\\n\\n[LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/fredhii) [X](https://x.com/Fredhii_) [GitHub](https://github.com/fredhii) [Medium](https://medium.com/@fredhii)\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://yangmao.ai/en/providers/cloudflare-workers-ai/free-tier\",\n      \"title\": \"Cloudflare Workers AI Free Tier, Signup Credits, and Limits ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Cloudflare Workers AI Free Tier, Signup Credits, and Limits ...\\nGenerated from the yangmao.ai provider database plus public provider documentation. Free credits, prices, and rate limits can change; verify in the official console before production.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://toolradar.com/tools/cloudflare-workers/pricing\",\n      \"title\": \"Cloudflare Workers Pricing 2026: Plans, Hidden Costs ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Skip to content do-not-click\\n\\nToolradar\\n\\nBrowse Alternatives Guides Research Work with us\\n\\nSearch tools... `⌘ K`\\n\\nList Your Product Join or Log In\\n\\nHome Tools Cloudflare Workers Pricing\\n\\nCloudflare Workers logo\\n\\n# Cloudflare Workers Pricing 2026\\n\\nPlans, hidden costs, and cheaper alternatives compared\\n\\nReviews on Capterra\\n\\n4 plans tracked · Updated Jun 2026\\n\\n## Is Cloudflare Workers worth the price?\\n\\n9/10\\n\\nCloudflare Workers at $5/month is among the cheapest serverless entry points, and the free tier (100K requests/day) is genuinely generous for prototyping.\\n\\nThe real cost emerges when you build a full-stack app on the Cloudflare ecosystem: KV storage ($0.50/GB-month), Durable Objects ($0.15/M requests + duration charges), D1 database ($0.001/M reads, $1.00/M writes), and R2 storage ($0.015/GB-month) all bill separately. A production app using Workers + KV + D1 + R2 typically costs $15-50/month — still cheap, but 3-10x the headline $5.\\nThe zero-egress-fee model on R2 is a genuine differentiator against AWS S3. CPU time (30M ms/month included) is the real constraint for compute-heavy workloads — image processing or PDF generation burns through it fast.\\n\\n## Pricing Plans\\n\\n### Free\\n\\nFree\\n\\n* 100k requests/day\\n* 10ms CPU time\\n* Limited KV storage\\n* No Durable Objects\\n* Good for testing\\n\\n### Paid\\n\\n$5 /monthly\\n\\n* 10M requests/month included\\n* 30M CPU-ms included\\n* $0.30/additional million requests\\n* $0.02/million CPU-ms overage\\n* Free egress and bandwidth\\n\\n### Workers for Platforms\\n\\n$25 /monthly\\n\\n* Multi-tenant apps\\n* Custom domains per tenant\\n* Platform-level features\\n\\n### Enterprise\\n\\nContact sales\\n\\n* Custom pricing\\n* Dedicated support\\n* SLAs\\n* Advanced features\\n\\nCalculate your cost [View full pricing](https://workers.cloudflare.com/pricing?utm_source=toolradar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=toolradar)\\n\\n## Hidden Costs & Gotchas\\n\\nCPU time is the real billing dimension, not requests.\\nThe included 30M CPU-ms sounds generous, but a single image-processing Worker using 50ms CPU per request exhausts it after just 600K requests/month — well under the 10M request allowance\\n\\nKV storage charges separately\\n\\n$0.50/M reads, $5.00/M writes, $0.50/GB-month storage. A medium-traffic cache with 5M reads and 500K writes/month adds $4.00/month on top of the base $5\\n\\nDurable Objects pricing is complex\\n\\n$0.15/M requests plus $12.50/M GB-seconds of duration. A real-time collaborative app with 1M DO requests and persistent WebSocket connections can easily cost $20-50/month in DO charges alone\\n\\nD1 database bills per row read/written after generous free tiers (25B reads, 50M writes). Heavy read workloads stay cheap, but write-heavy apps at $1.00/M rows written add up: 10M writes/month = $10/month extra\\n\\nR2 storage has no egress fees but Class A operations (writes, lists) cost $4.50/M.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.truefoundry.com/blog/cloudflare-ai-gateway-pricing\",\n      \"title\": \"Cloudflare AI Gateway Pricing Explained For 2026\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"But as systems move toward production scale, priorities shift to **cost control, observability, compliance, and flexibility** .\\n\\nPlatforms like [**TrueFoundry**](https://www.truefoundry.com/) are built for teams scaling AI in production where infrastructure ownership, data privacy, and usage-based budgeting matter deeply.\\n\\nOne scaling startup migrated from Cloudflare to TrueFoundry after unpredictable logging costs began exceeding compute budgets. By switching to a **self-hosted gateway in their AWS VPC** , they achieved **35% cost reduction** , unified logging to S3, and routed traffic to a mix of OpenAI and private Mistral models - all with clear per-team budget controls.\\n\\nYou can get similar results for your organization as well. [Book a demo](https://www.truefoundry.com/book-demo?ref=/blog/cloudflare-ai-gateway-pricing) to see how TrueFoundry can bring AI cost predictability and control to your team.\\n\\n## **Frequently asked questions**\\n\\n### **Is Cloudflare AI Gateway free?**\\nYes, Cloudflare offers free access to AI Gateway features under its standard and Workers Paid tiers. However, usage limits, log retention policies, and underlying compute (e.g., Workers CPU time) may introduce hidden costs as scale increases.\\n\\n### **How much will Cloudflare AI cost?**\\n\\nCloudflare AI Gateway itself has no per-request fee. Costs emerge based on:\\n\\n* Log volume and retention (e.g., 100,000 logs on free tier, 1M on Workers Paid)\\n* Worker usage for request processing and routing\\n* Cloudflare plan level (e.g., Standard vs Enterprise)\\n\\nPricing can become unpredictable at high volume without custom plans or external log management. TrueFoundry offers a better alternative; you can find the [pricing here.](https://www.truefoundry.com/pricing)\\n\\n### **How is TrueFoundry more cost-effective than Cloudflare AI?**\\n\\nTrueFoundry runs entirely inside your own cloud (AWS, GCP, Azure), eliminating data transfer costs and SaaS markups.\\nYou pay only for the compute and storage you allocate — with full routing flexibility, transparent logs, and no vendor lock-in. Teams can also route to private models or use spot instances to reduce cost by 60–70% versus managed APIs.\\n\\nTrueFoundry AI Gateway delivers ~3–4 ms latency, handles 350+ RPS on 1 vCPU, scales horizontally with ease, and is production-ready, while LiteLLM suffers from high latency, struggles beyond moderate RPS, lacks built-in scaling, and is best for light or prototype workloads.\\n\\nBuilt for Speed: ~10ms Latency, Even Under Load\\n\\nSchedule your Demo Now\\n\\n## The fastest way to build, govern and scale your AI\\n\\nHow Can You Prevent GenAI Costs From Spiraling at Scale?\\n\\nGartner report on best practices for optimizing generative and agentic AI costs and projected statistics.\\n\\n[Access Full 2026 Report](https://www.truefoundry.com/gartner-2026-best-practice-for-optimizing-agentic-ai-costs?utm_source=widget&utm_medium=blog)\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://yangmao.ai/en/providers/cloudflare-workers-ai/api-pricing\",\n      \"title\": \"Cloudflare Workers AI API Pricing and Free Trial\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Cloudflare Workers AI API Pricing and Free Trial\\nCloudflare Workers AI API free credits, pricing notes, rate limits, OpenAI SDK compatibility, relay options, and lower-cost alternatives.\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"warnings\": null,\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"session_id\": \"ses_133b65566ffeVnr57162W4Xqf3\"\n}",
