      "text": "Now I have the full picture. Let me summarize what Cloudflare Workers AI offers for free and whether ProLector can run inference on it.\n\nKey findings:\n1. Cloudflare Workers AI has TTS models: `@cf/deepgram/aura-1`, `@cf/deepgram/aura-2-en`, `@cf/deepgram/aura-2-es`\n2. Free tier: 10,000 neurons/day\n3. The problem: Kokoro-82M, F5-TTS, Chatterbox are NOT on Cloudflare Workers AI - they're self-hosted models\n\n\n4. The models Cloudflare does have are LLMs, image gen, embeddings, Whisper for speech recognition, and Deepgram TTS - but not the specific ones ProLector needs.\n\nSo the architecture question becomes whether ProLector can actually run on Cloudflare's free tier, and the answer is complicated: the models they want to use simply aren't available there, and even the ones that are would be severely constrained by the neuron limits.",
