    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Here's the honest answer:\n\n## What Cloudflare Workers AI actually has for TTS\n\n| Model | Available? | Free Tier |\n|---|---|---|\n| Kokoro-82M | ❌ No | — |\n| F5-TTS | ❌ No | — |\n| Chatterbox | ❌ No | — |\n| **Deepgram Aura** | ✅ Yes | 10,000 neurons/day |\n| Deepgram Aura-2 | ✅ Yes | 10,000 neurons/day |\n\nDeepgram Aura is a good TTS model. But it's **not** what ProLector uses. ProLector runs Kokoro-82M, F5-TTS, and Chatterbox — none of which are on Cloudflare's platform.\n\n## The real constraint\n\nCloudflare Workers AI free tier = **10,000 neurons/day**. For reference:\n- One TTS request (1 sentence, ~20 words) ≈ 200-500 neurons\n- That's roughly **20-50 TTS requests/day** on free tier\n- A 5-minute teleprompter session needs ~30-50 sentences\n- **One user, one session = most of the daily quota**\n\n## What would actually work\n\n**Option A: Hybrid (what ProLector already does)**\n- Browser-side Kokoro via WebAssembly = **$0 forever**\n- No Cloudflare compute needed\n- The model downloads once, caches in OPFS\n\n**Option B: Cloudflare Deepgram fallback**\n- Use `@cf/deepgram/aura-1` as a cloud fallback\n- Free for light use (a few sessions/day)\n- Falls back to browser-side Kokoro when quota is hit\n- I can wire this up as a 6th engine in SyllabusMirror\n\n**Option C: The real free move**\n- ProLector already runs inference for free in the browser\n- Cloudflare Pages hosts the static site for free\n- Total cost: $0.00\n\nThe models you chose (Kokoro, F5-TTS, Chatterbox) are specifically the ones that run locally for free. That was the right architecture choice. Cloudflare's free AI doesn't add anything you don't already have.\n\nWant me to add Deepgram Aura as a cloud fallback engine, or is the current browser-side approach enough?",
      "timestamp": 1781546216557
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I have the full picture. Let me give the user a clear, honest answer.\n\nKey findings:\n1. Cloudflare Workers AI has TTS models: `@cf/deepgram/aura-1`, `@cf/deepgram/aura-2-en` — these are Deepgram's TTS models\n2. Kokoro-82M, F5-TTS, Chatterbox are NOT on Cloudflare Workers AI\n3. Cloudflare Workers AI free tier: 10,000 neurons/day\n4. The current ProLector architecture is browser-side (WebAssembly)\n\n\n5. Running TTS on Cloudflare would require a Worker that calls their API, but the models aren't available there — you'd be limited to Deepgram's offerings, and the 10K neuron daily limit is a hard constraint.",
