    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user wants me to address all 7 gaps identified in the analysis:\n\n1. No explanation of what \"prosody\" means on first visit\n2. No onboarding flow for non-technical users\n3. No guidance on what WPM to start with\n4. No progress tracking across sessions\n5. No teacher/classroom mode\n6. No non-English language support\n7. No dialect selection beyond the 6 Kokoro voices\n\nThis is a big set of features. Let me plan this out:\n\n1. **Prosody explainer** - Add a tooltip/inline definition on first visit, maybe a dismissible banner or a \"What is prosody?\" link\n\n\n2. **Onboarding flow** - Create a first-visit wizard that walks through the basics\n3. **WPM guidance** - Add a WPM recommender based on language level\n4. **Progress tracking** - Build a session history system with localStorage\n5. **Teacher/classroom mode** - Add a teacher dashboard view\n6. **Non-English support** - Add language selection\n7. **Dialect selection** - Expand voice options\n\nI need to tackle these systematically, starting with the simpler UI additions like the prosody explainer and WPM guidance, then moving toward the more complex features like progress tracking and teacher mode.\n\nFor the onboarding flow, I'll create a first-visit wizard that greets new users. Progress tracking needs a stats system that persists to localStorage. The teacher/classroom mode will be a separate route for managing students. Language and dialect support require extending the existing voice configuration system.\n\nLet me start implementing these features.",
